{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3356","heading":"Exemption from appraisals of real estate located in rural areas","label":"3356 Exemption from appraisals of real estate located in rural areas","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/ch34A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definitions","label":"a Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the term “mortgage originator” has the meaning given the term in ; andsection 1602 of title 15","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the term “transaction value” means the amount of a loan or extension of credit, including a loan or extension of credit that is part of a pool of loans or extensions of credit.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Appraisal not required","label":"b Appraisal not required","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the real property or interest in real property is located in a rural area, as described in section 1026.35(b)(2)(iv)(A) of title 12, Code of Federal Regulations;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has contacted not fewer than 3 State certified appraisers or State licensed appraisers, as applicable, on the mortgage originator’s approved appraiser list in the market area in accordance with part 226 of title 12, Code of Federal Regulations; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has documented that no State certified appraiser or State licensed appraiser, as applicable, was available within 5 business days beyond customary and reasonable fee and timeliness standards for comparable appraisal assignments, as documented by the mortgage originator or its agent;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the transaction value is less than $400,000; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the mortgage originator is subject to oversight by a Federal financial institutions regulatory agency.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Sale, assignment, or transfer","label":"c Sale, assignment, or transfer","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the loan is sold, assigned, or otherwise transferred to another person by reason of the bankruptcy or failure of the mortgage originator;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the loan is sold, assigned, or otherwise transferred to another person regulated by a Federal financial institutions regulatory agency, so long as the loan is retained in portfolio by the person;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the sale, assignment, or transfer is pursuant to a merger of the mortgage originator with another person or the acquisition of the mortgage originator by another person or of another person by the mortgage originator; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the sale, loan, or transfer is to a wholly owned subsidiary of the mortgage originator, provided that, after the sale, assignment, or transfer, the loan is considered to be an asset of the mortgage originator for regulatory accounting purposes.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Exception","label":"d Exception","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a Federal financial institutions regulatory agency requires an appraisal under section 225.63(c), 323.3(c), 34.43(c), or 722.3(e) of title 12, Code of Federal Regulations; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the loan is a high-cost mortgage, as defined in .section 1602 of title 15","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Anti-evasion","label":"e Anti-evasion","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t12/s3356","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft12%2Fs3356%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Each Federal financial institutions regulatory agency shall ensure that any mortgage originator that the Federal financial institutions regulatory agency oversees that makes a significant amount of loans under subsection (b) is complying with the requirements of subsection (b)(2) with respect to each loan.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
